column9: Video 1 is bizarre, but it's amusing and fun. I like the setting and story. Video 2 is less fun, has more swearing, and I don't like the song as much, though neither of them are really my style.

There really isn't much to the first video. Video 2, "Hello," is such a powerful song. Story the video tells is perhaps a bit expected, following the lyrics as literally as it does. Still I like it better than the first.

Video 1 evokes emotions, which made it very engaging. It was a good mix of song and video. But ultimately it was unsatisfying. Video 2 has a more fun feel to the video, but it doesn't match well with the song. Still, the story made it more fun overall.
Video 1 looked more homemade and told an interesting story, which I liked. Video 2 has a lot more expletives than I like to listen to.
I think video 2 will probably appeal to a wider audience.

The genre of music in video 1 is more relevant to the interests of me and my friends so even though I think the video is kind of dumb I still enjoyed it because of the music. I also think that because video 1 uses a song that is probably better known it will probably have a few more views than video 2.
